			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				There is a easy way to finance your blcksmithing, but it takes a little more time. What I did was practice tailoring until i got to where i could easily make things. Tailoring is not that expensive, because all you have to do is kill to get pelts, and buy the patterns, and of course have a sewing kit. Any way, you sell the armor that you make from tailoring and use it to get your supplies for blacksmithing. This is also good, because when you get good enough to make studs, you can use them to make studded armor, which sells for even more than the patchwork. Well, that is my 2 cents, hope it helps you and good luck<BR>
<BR>
Barbwyre (Barbarian Warrior)<BR>
soon to be Master of the Arts
