				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				When i hit 21 i started making toolboxes im only at level 36 but they seem to be the simplest thing to make 1 water 1 bit, plus when since it has 8 slots and only weighs 0.4 pounds after you make as many as you can hold you switch to file, scaler, whatever and now you have tons of storage space.  Plus I hardly fail and I raise skill kinda quickly. My main problem is the long drawn out process of buying and making bits.  You buy 100 ore and then start making bits, after the fiftieth time of seeing &quot;you do not advance from this&quot; you feel like blowing your brain out.  A couple of questions, is there anything that you loot ore from? If so is it low level?  They make spidersilks loot off large spiders for tailors but blacksmiths have to buy ore.  Plus why cant we use foraged or summoned water? What is the purpose of denying us that.  2ore + 1 water equals bit, but 2 spider silks equal one silk patch.  See they dont use water and get away with it, therefore I think we should be able to use foraged/summoned.  sorry for ranting 
