	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				First of all if you ever get down to around 20-30 plat start making metal bits, then you can use those metal bits (3) one File, and one Flask of water, and make studs Your success rate isnt great until around 80 skill with the studs and they take a long time to make but you get 2 studs per success, and you can normally find a Tailor willing to buy studs for 1pp each. and the Tailors often buy them 40 or more at a time.  Selling studs is how I financed my blacksmithing until i got to 100-110 skill where you can really stick with just banded to make your profit and skill up.  Time consuming but effective.<BR>
Second you can buy Fine Plate molds in Freeport (medium) and Halas, (Large)  I have not found where the small is sold, but i would expect that to be in the Halfling/Gnome/dwarven cities, possibly any of the Elven cities too. the Medium FP molds are on the Second Floor of the Armory in East Freeport (same building you buy the banded in) and the Large is sold in the Warrior guild (i think) in Halas, it is the one with the ramp winding up the inside of the building, also i think it is the tallesst building in Halas being about 3 stories if I recall correctly.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

